library(jsonlite)
library(ggplot2)

library(knitr)

# load utility functions
source("./mobqol_util.R")

# define dimension ID
ds_dims = c("AC","CO","PD","IN","SE","ME","AX")

1.2 Load raw data

# load eligible id 
eligible_ids = read.csv("GP.csv")$Survey.ID
# load raw response data
mq_jsons = read_json("raw_responses.json")
# retrieve and process data from JSON
mq = retrieveMobQoLPUFs(raw_jsons = mq_jsons, eligible_ids = eligible_ids)

1.8 Dimension weights

dim_weights = by(mq$weights_df$value, mq$weights_df$dim_id, \(dim){
  cbind(
    paste(round(mean(dim),1), " (",round(sd(dim),1),")",sep = ""),
    paste(round(median(dim),1), " (",paste0(round(quantile(dim,c(0.25,0.75))),collapse = "; "),")",sep = "")
  )
})

dim_weights_tbl = do.call(rbind, dim_weights)
rownames(dim_weights_tbl) = names(dim_weights)
kable(dim_weights_tbl, col.names = c("Mean (SD)","Median (IQR)"))

1.9 Level ratings

lvl_ratings = lapply(ds_dims,\(dim){
    s_ = grepl(dim,mq$ratings_df$lvl_id) & !grepl("_3",mq$ratings_df$lvl_id) & !grepl("_0",mq$ratings_df$lvl_id)
    df_ = mq$ratings_df[s_,]
    x = by(df_$value,df_$lvl_id,\(lvl){
      cbind(
        paste(round(mean(lvl),1), " (",round(sd(lvl),1),")",sep = ""),
        paste(round(median(lvl),1), " (",paste0(round(quantile(lvl,c(0.25,0.75))),collapse = "; "),")",sep = "")
      )
    })
    x = do.call(rbind, x)
    x = rbind(c("",""),x)
    rownames(x) = c(dim,"lvl2","lvl3")
    x
  })

lvl_ratings_tbl = do.call(rbind, lvl_ratings)

1.10 Anchoring

n (%) Participants indicated they would prefer the worst state over being dead: 331 (66%)

n (%) Participants indicated they would prefer being dead over the worst state or be indifferent: 173 (34%)

# Distribution of the utility value of the worst health state
1-quantile(mq$anchor_df$anchor, c(0,0.25,0.5,0.75,1))
##            0%           25%           50%           75%          100% 
##    1.00000000    0.49665000    0.17810000   -0.03678052 -453.54545455
# NOTE: 1 EXTREME (!!) outlier has utility of -453 !
# This has a significant effect on mean and sd
1-mean(mq$anchor_df$anchor);sd(mq$anchor_df$anchor);
## [1] -2.095747
## [1] 25.13367
# Thus: trim anchor points to -1 (this is commonly done)
mq_trimmed = mq$anchor_df$anchor
# Affects the anchor point of 
sum(mq_trimmed> 2) # n participants
## [1] 29
round(sum(mq_trimmed> 2)/mq$n_pufs*100) # %
## [1] 6
# trim
mq_trimmed[mq_trimmed> 2] = 2
# without the outliers, new mean anchor point is quite different:
1-mean(mq_trimmed);sd(mq_trimmed);
## [1] 0.1714396
## [1] 0.4719166
# distribution of achor points
ggplot() +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_histogram(aes(1-mq_trimmed), col = "black", fill = "lightblue", alpha = 0.9, binwidth = 0.1) +
  xlab("Utility of the worst state") +
  theme_minimal()

1.11 Social value set

# Social preference model
mq_mean_est = formatC(apply(mq$pufs_trimmed,2,mean),digits = 3, format = "f")
mq_mean_boot = replicate(10000,apply(mq$pufs_trimmed[sample(1:nrow(mq$pufs_trimmed),size = nrow(mq$pufs_trimmed),replace = T),],2,mean))
mq_mean_boot = formatC(apply(mq_mean_boot,1,quantile,probs = c(0.025,0.975)),digits = 3, format = "f")
mq_m_95 = sapply(1:ncol(mq_mean_boot), \(i) paste(mq_mean_est[i]," (",mq_mean_boot[1,i],"; ",mq_mean_boot[2,i],")",sep = ""))
mq_m_95 = matrix(mq_m_95, ncol = length(ds_dims))[-1,]
colnames(mq_m_95) = ds_dims
rownames(mq_m_95) = paste("lvl_",1:nrow(mq_m_95))
kable(mq_m_95)
AC CO PD IN SE ME AX
lvl_ 1 0.063 (0.057; 0.070) 0.054 (0.049; 0.059) 0.068 (0.061; 0.076) 0.033 (0.030; 0.037) 0.046 (0.042; 0.050) 0.055 (0.050; 0.060) 0.044 (0.040; 0.049)
lvl_ 2 0.106 (0.098; 0.116) 0.082 (0.075; 0.089) 0.111 (0.102; 0.122) 0.072 (0.066; 0.078) 0.068 (0.062; 0.075) 0.084 (0.076; 0.093) 0.073 (0.067; 0.079)
lvl_ 3 0.148 (0.137; 0.159) 0.121 (0.112; 0.130) 0.160 (0.148; 0.173) 0.124 (0.115; 0.134) 0.098 (0.091; 0.105) 0.119 (0.110; 0.130) 0.101 (0.094; 0.109) 
# social value set
social_model = matrix(apply(mq$pufs_trimmed,2,mean), ncol = length(ds_dims))
ds_expanded = expand.grid(lapply(1:7, \(x) 1:4))
ds_str = apply(ds_expanded,1,\(x) paste0(x,collapse=""))
mq_vs = c()
for(i in 1:nrow(ds_expanded)){
  v_ = 1
  for(j in seq_along(ds_expanded[i,])){
    v_ = v_ - social_model[ds_expanded[i,j],j]
  }
  mq_vs = c(mq_vs, v_)
}

mq_hs_ranking = order(-mq_vs)
# trimmed utility ranges
ggplot() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, col = "gray", size = 0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(x = 1:length(mq_hs_ranking), y = mq_vs[mq_hs_ranking])) +
  ylab("HRQoL / Utility") +
  xlab("MobQoL states - ranked from best to worst") +
  theme_minimal()
